Package: maxima
Version: 5.9pre
Revision: 12
Maintainer: William McCallum <wmc@math.arizona.edu>
Description: Symbol manipulation program
Source: mirror:sourceforge:fink/%n-%v.tar.gz
SourceDirectory:maxima
Depends: clisp (>= 2.2.9-2)
BuildDepends:autoconf25, automake
License: GPL
ConfigureParams: --prefix='${prefix}' --exec-prefix='${prefix}' --infodir='${prefix}/share/info' --mandir='${prefix}/share/man' --libexecdir='${prefix}/lib'
CompileScript:<<
  ./bootstrap	
  ./configure %c
  sed s/\$\{prefix\}/\\%p/g interfaces/xmaxima/autoconf-variables.tcl > autoconf-variables.tcl.new
  sed s/\$\{prefix\}/\\%p/g src/autoconf-variables.lisp > autoconf-variables.lisp.new
  sed s/\$\{prefix\}/\\%p/g src/maxima > maxima.new
  mv autoconf-variables.tcl.new interfaces/xmaxima/autoconf-variables.tcl 
  mv autoconf-variables.lisp.new src/autoconf-variables.lisp 
  mv maxima.new src/maxima 
  make prefix=%p
<<
DocFiles: AUTHORS COPYING COPYING1 INSTALL README
InfoDocs: maxima.info
DescDetail:<<
Maxima is a descendant of the symbol manipulation program Macsyma, 
which had its roots in the late 1960s at MIT. Its abilities include 
basic algebraic manipulation, symbolic integration, 2D and 3D plotting, 
and an ODE solver. 
<<
DescUsage:<<
If you have trouble installing with Fink Commander, try installing from
the command line (and don't divert the output to a file).

Enter "maxima"  to get a command line interface, and "xmaxima" to get 
a graphical interface under xwindows. In XDarwin's rootless mode there
are problems with menus not working, maxima refusing to quit, and 
the window refusing to come to the front even though active. You
should be o.k. in rootless mode if you use the icewm windowmanager and 
don't have any other xwindows open. Note this is a 
prerelease version of 5.9 and is unsupported by the developers. 
<<
